<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. OVipositor (
<figureCitation box="[567,660,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
): Coxite length about 2.9 times width, with microchaetae. Styli subcylindrical, length about 1.2 times width, with 7 macrochaetae. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1145,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) C-shaped, no nodulus or ramus; cornu as broad as the corpus, with a small apical protuberance. Spiculum Ventrale (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1314,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) elongate, straight, apical plate membranous and setiferous.
</paragraph>
